ArcSafe — security-fixes.patch
Remediation pass 2026-07-20. Maps to security-report.md §9.

NOTE: the working tree is NOT under version control (no .git), so this is a
documented, file-by-file change list rather than a `git diff` / `git apply`
patch. No secret value appears anywhere in this file. Once the tree is under
git, `git diff` will reproduce these same hunks.

================================================================================
SEC-004 — CREATE2 collision now reverts with a named, decodable error
================================================================================

--- contracts/ArcSafeFactory.sol  (createSafe)
    Added, after computing scopedSalt and before `new ArcSafe{salt}`:

+       // Fail with a named error the UI can explain when this exact
+       // (deployer, salt, owners, threshold) tuple was already deployed.
+       // Without this the CREATE2 collision reverts with no decodable reason.
+       address predicted = _predict(scopedSalt, owners, threshold);
+       if (predicted.code.length != 0) revert SafeAlreadyExists();

--- contracts/ArcSafeFactory.sol  (predictAddress -> shared _predict helper)
    predictAddress now delegates the CREATE2 math to a private _predict() so the
    collision guard and the public predictor can never diverge:

-   function predictAddress(...) external view returns (address) {
-       bytes32 scopedSalt = keccak256(abi.encodePacked(deployer, salt));
-       bytes32 initCodeHash = keccak256(abi.encodePacked(type(ArcSafe).creationCode, abi.encode(owners, threshold)));
-       return address(uint160(uint256(keccak256(abi.encodePacked(bytes1(0xff), address(this), scopedSalt, initCodeHash)))));
-   }
+   function predictAddress(...) external view returns (address) {
+       return _predict(keccak256(abi.encodePacked(deployer, salt)), owners, threshold);
+   }
+
+   function _predict(bytes32 scopedSalt, address[] calldata owners, uint256 threshold)
+       private view returns (address)
+   {
+       bytes32 initCodeHash = keccak256(abi.encodePacked(type(ArcSafe).creationCode, abi.encode(owners, threshold)));
+       return address(uint160(uint256(keccak256(abi.encodePacked(bytes1(0xff), address(this), scopedSalt, initCodeHash)))));
+   }

--- frontend/src/lib/config.ts  (FACTORY_ABI)
    Declared the factory's custom errors so ethers can decode a revert:

+   'error NoOwners()',
+   'error SafeAlreadyExists()',

--- frontend/src/lib/format.ts  (humanizeError map)
    Mapped the new errors to plain sentences:

+   SafeAlreadyExists: 'A safe with these exact owners and threshold already exists at this address. Change the owners or threshold, or try again to get a fresh address.',
+   NoOwners: 'A safe needs at least one owner.',

--- test/ArcSafe.test.js  (ArcSafeFactory describe block)
    Added regression test:
    "rejects a repeat deployment with a named error instead of an opaque revert"
    Asserts a duplicate createSafe reverts with SafeAlreadyExists and leaves the
    index untouched. Suite: 42 -> 43 passing.

  ON-CHAIN NOTE: this changes factory bytecode. Redeploy the factory to carry
  the fix on-chain; existing safes are unaffected (ArcSafe bytecode unchanged,
  so predicted safe addresses are stable).

================================================================================
SEC-002 — Security response headers (CSP/HSTS/XFO/nosniff/Referrer/...)
================================================================================

--- deploy/nginx-arcsafe.conf   (NEW FILE)
    HTTPS server block serving the static export at /arcsafe/, with:
      Content-Security-Policy (script-src 'self'; connect-src scoped to
        https://rpc.testnet.arc.network + https://arc-testnet.rpc.thirdweb.com;
        frame-ancestors 'none'; base-uri 'self'; object-src 'none')
      Strict-Transport-Security (2y, includeSubDomains)
      X-Frame-Options: DENY
      X-Content-Type-Options: nosniff
      Referrer-Policy: no-referrer
      Permissions-Policy (camera/microphone/geolocation/payment denied)
      Cross-Origin-Opener-Policy: same-origin
      HTTP->HTTPS redirect; immutable caching for _next/static.
    ACTION: install over TLS on the VPS (steps in the file header), then verify
    with the curl command in security-report.md §12.

--- frontend/src/pages/_app.tsx   (<Head>)
    Document-level control that works even before the server block is deployed:

+   <meta name="referrer" content="no-referrer" />

================================================================================
SEC-001 — Guard against future private-key exposure (rotation stays owner-only)
================================================================================

--- scripts/check-secrets.js   (NEW FILE)
    Scans the working tree (excluding node_modules/.env/build outputs) for the
    .env PRIVATE_KEY value or any hardcoded key-like 64-hex assignment; exits 1
    on a hit; redacts every match. Confirmed clean on this tree.

--- package.json   (scripts)
+   "check:secrets": "node scripts/check-secrets.js",

  The key value itself was NOT modified — rotation is an irreversible action
  only the key owner can safely perform. See security-report.md §5 (SEC-001).

